statistics.name: assists
statistics.description: The number of times a player who passes the ball to a teammate in a way that leads to a score by field goal, meaning that he or she was "assisting" in the basket. There is some judgment involved in deciding whether a passer should be credited with an assist.

statistics.description: The average number of assists a player or team records per turnover

article.headline: Yale 101, St. Joseph's (NY) 86
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Greg Mangano scored 35 points and had 22 rebounds, both career highs, as Yale withstood a challenge from Division III opponent St. Joseph's (Long Island) for a 101-86 victory Sunday. The Bulldogs (10-4) raced to a 29-4 lead in less than 7 minutes against the Golden Eagles (10-2), who had never before played a Division I team. But led by Chris Jimenez, St. Joseph's made a game of it. Jimenez scored 15 of his 22 points, including four 3-pointers, in a 34-12 St. Joseph's run that cut Yale's lead to 41-38. It was 46-43 Yale at halftime. Led by Mangano, the Bulldogs quickly reasserted themselves in the second half. The senior center made a layup and a 3-pointer in the opening minute, as Yale built a 67-54 lead with 6:44 gone and never led by fewer than 10 points after that. Reggie Willhite added 19 points for Yale.
